com.hyperwallet.android

Class Hyperwallet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hyperwallet.android.Hyperwallet

  • public class Hyperwallet
extends Object
    The Hyperwallet class is an Android specific implementation of the Hyperwallet platform User APIs.

    A single instance of the Hyperwallet class is maintained. Resetting the current instance by calling getInstance(HyperwalletAuthenticationTokenProvider) is critical when switching between authenticated Users. Failure to do so will result in incorrect access and incorrect modifications to User data.

    Authentication with the Hyperwallet platform is accomplished through the usage of JSON Web Tokens. At instantiation an HyperwalletAuthenticationTokenProvider is set as a member variable to provide the Hyperwallet class with an authentication token upon request.

    Method invocations that require a HyperwalletListener will either process the request in the current thread or in a background thread depending on if the HyperwalletListener.getHandler() returns null or not.

        public static Hyperwallet getInstance(HyperwalletAuthenticationTokenProvider hyperwalletAuthenticationTokenProvider)
        Creates a new instance of the Hyperwallet Core SDK interface object. If a previously created instance exists, it will be replaced.
        Parameters:
        hyperwalletAuthenticationTokenProvider - a provider of Hyperwallet authentication tokens; must not be null
        Returns:
        A Hyperwallet instance

      • getInstance

        public static Hyperwallet getInstance(HyperwalletAuthenticationTokenProvider hyperwalletAuthenticationTokenProvider,
                                      HyperwalletListener<Configuration> listener)
        Creates a new instance of the Hyperwallet Core SDK interface object. If a previously created instance exists, it will be replaced. In addition to getInstance(HyperwalletAuthenticationTokenProvider), is a listener object HyperwalletListener this means that this method will eagerly authenticate. if it does not fit your use case please use the former.

        Moreover a callback is provided to listen if authentication is successful or not, if successful, a Configuration object is passed over the listener through HyperwalletListener.onSuccess(Object); otherwise HyperwalletListener.onFailure(HyperwalletException) is invoked with details on the error.

        Parameters:
        hyperwalletAuthenticationTokenProvider - a provider of Hyperwallet authentication tokens; must not be null
        listener - the callback handler of responses from the Hyperwallet platform; must not be null

      • getDefault

        public static Hyperwallet getDefault()
        Returns the previously initialized instance of the Hyperwallet Core SDK interface object.
        Returns:
        A previously initialized instance of Hyperwallet; maintaining its HyperwalletAuthenticationTokenProvider
        Throws:
        HyperwalletInitializationException - if this Hyperwallet object was not initialized with getInstance(HyperwalletAuthenticationTokenProvider)

      • getConfiguration

        public void getConfiguration(HyperwalletListener<Configuration> listener)
        Retrieves the Configuration based on the values from the Authentication Token Provider. Please be aware that this method will also authenticate, if for instance there's a previous authentication that is still valid then the valid Configuration will be provided in HyperwalletListener.onSuccess(Object)
        Parameters:
        listener - the callback handler of responses from the Hyperwallet platform; must not be null

      • createBankAccount

        public void createBankAccount(BankAccount bankAccount,
                              HyperwalletListener<BankAccount> listener)
        Creates a BankAccount for the User associated with the authentication token returned from HyperwalletAuthenticationTokenProvider.retrieveAuthenticationToken(HyperwalletAuthenticationTokenListener).

        The HyperwalletListener that is passed in to this method invocation will receive the responses from processing the request.

        This function will request a new authentication token via HyperwalletAuthenticationTokenProvider if the current one is expired or about to expire.

        Parameters:
        bankAccount - the BankAccount to be created; must not be null
        listener - the callback handler of responses from the Hyperwallet platform; must not be null

      • listBankAccounts

        public void listBankAccounts(BankAccountQueryParam queryParam,
                             HyperwalletListener<PageList<BankAccount>> listener)
        Returns the list of BankAccounts for the User associated with the authentication token returned from HyperwalletAuthenticationTokenProvider.retrieveAuthenticationToken(HyperwalletAuthenticationTokenListener), or an empty List if non exist.

        The ordering and filtering of BankAccounts will be based on the criteria specified within the BankAccountQueryParam object, if it is not null. Otherwise the default ordering and filtering will be applied:

        • Offset: 0
        • Limit: 10
        • Created Before: N/A
        • Created After: N/A
        • Type: Bank Account
        • Status: All
        • Sort By: Created On

        The HyperwalletListener that is passed in to this method invocation will receive the responses from * processing the request.

        This function will request a new authentication token via HyperwalletAuthenticationTokenProvider if the current one is expired or about to expire.

        Parameters:
        queryParam - the ordering and filtering criteria
        listener - the callback handler of responses from the Hyperwallet platform; must not be null
